<div class="intro-pull"><strong>Ashley National Forest is in Vernal's backyard.</strong> The forest boundary starts approximately 15 miles north of Best Western Vernal Inn along Highway 191. Whether you're here for elk hunting season, backpacking the High Uintas, fly fishing mountain streams, or riding ATV trails through forest roads, our hotel is the last full-service lodging before you head into the backcountry. Stock up in town, sleep in a real bed, and hit the trailhead fresh. Rates start at $84/night, or $588 for a full week.</div>
<div class="content-section">
 <h2>Your Basecamp for the Uintas</h2>
<p>From Best Western Vernal Inn, the Ashley National Forest boundary is approximately 15 miles north on Highway 191. From there, access roads lead to trailheads, campgrounds, fishing streams, and some of the most remote wilderness in the lower 48 — the High Uintas Wilderness Area, home to Kings Peak, Utah's highest point at 13,528 feet. Vernal is the last town with hotels, groceries, gas, and outfitters before you enter the forest.</p>
<ul class="feat-list">
 <li>~15 miles to the forest boundary via Hwy 191</li>
 <li>Access to High Uintas Wilderness trailheads</li>
 <li>Free hot breakfast — fuel up before trailhead drives</li>
